ry after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Falaise was born in 1025, in Falaise, Calvados, Lower Normandy, France as the son of Walter De Falaise. He had at least 1 son with Alberade Moulins-La Marché. He died on 19 October 1100, in Moulins, Calvados, Lower Normandy, France, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1025–19 October 1100":"1025–19. oktoober 1100","1025–1100":"1025–1100","1030–Female":"1030–Surnud","1030–1122":"1030–1122","1050–1093":"1050–1093","1006–1100":"1006–1100","1006":"1006","1025":"1025","19 OCT 1100":"19. oktoober 1100","1122":"1122","1100":"1100","19 October 1100":"19. oktoober 1100","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","1093":"1093","Falaise, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Falaise, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Moulins, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Moulins, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Moulins, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Moulins, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1025–19 October 1100":"1025–19. lokakuuta 1100","1025–1100":"1025–1100","1030–Female":"1030–Kuollut","1030–1122":"1030–1122","1050–1093":"1050–1093","1006–1100":"1006–1100","1006":"1006","1025":"1025","19 OCT 1100":"19. lokakuuta 1100","1122":"1122","1100":"1100","19 October 1100":"19. lokakuuta 1100","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","1093":"1093","Falaise, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Falaise, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Moulins, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Moulins, Calvados, Normandie, Ranska","Moulins, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Moulins, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1025–19 October 1100":"1025–19 octobre 1100","1025–1100":"1025–1100","1030–Female":"1030–Décédée","1030–1122":"1030–1122","1050–1093":"1050–1093","1006–1100":"1006–1100","1006":"1006","1025":"1025","19 OCT 1100"